pageContext.claim: “The lowest unemployment rate we've ever had -- you could say "51 years" or you could say "ever." But groups -- if you look at African American, Asian American, Hispanic American -- the lowest unemployment rate, historically, ever.”
pageContext.analysis: The unemployment rate was 3.7 percent in November 2018. Since then it has picked up, hitting 4 percent in January 2019 then to 3.8 percent in February 2019. The unemployment rate is now only the lowest in six months. Plus, it's been below 3.7 percent several times in 1958 or 61 years ago.
